pr_review_comment_body:
@benjello since it is only for 2013 is the notation ok ?
Plus, this implementation of the reform might not allow to use reform_tax_benfit_system for any other year than 2013 ?
@cbenz does a Dated formula reform modify just the dated function concerned or does it modify all the class (and thus you end with just one dated_function implemented in your reform) ?

Should definitely change this to a check, I think? Could then do (or this could be abstracted further):
```
if (!_checkChannels(store, channelId, _channelListState(channelsData))) {
    handleError('Channel not Found');
    return;
}
```

I think that given than the only case we want to handle is `OR`, it could be refactored as:
```python
def add_filter(self, filter_values:
    if OR_OPERATOR not in filter_values:
        return super(TermsFacet, self).add_filter(filter_values)
    values = filter_values.split(OR_OPERATOR)
    return any(super(TermsFacet, self).add_filter(v) for v in values)
```
And so it preserve the parent logic.
What do you think about ?

Looks like there is a bug in the Python 2 part, `args.encode('utf8')`. 

I think you could simplify this method by encoded (or not) at the end - didn't test it though. 
```python
def create_title(plugin=None):
	if args.title and plugin:
        title = args.title.format(title=plugin._get_title(),
                                  author=plugin._get_author(),
                                  category=plugin._get_category(),
                                  game=plugin._get_category())
    else:
        title = args.url

	if is_py2:
        return title.encode("utf8")
	else:
        return title
```
